cs.IR, cs.CSCW, cs.HCI, cs.DL, cs.SI 

This paper discusses the design of collaborative information retrieval systems and explores collaborative information behavior in organizational settings. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses methodology for collecting data on collaborative information behavior, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.CSCW (Computer-Supported Cooperative Work) and cs.HCI (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the paper mentions gathering requirements for the design of these systems, which could fall under cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
